Package: StaBITUFS
Type: Package
Title: Stability-Based Information-Theoretic Unsupervised Feature Selection for scRNA-seq
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: person(given = "Maitreya Sameer", family = "Ganu",
    email = "maitreyaganu@gmail.com", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: Two unsupervised feature-selection methods for single-cell RNA
    sequencing count data. PLit (Parametric Length Information Test) ranks genes
    by a two-part minimum-description-length code-length gap against a fitted
    parametric null; the unpenalised score equals n times an empirical
    Kullback-Leibler divergence. ReThiN (Reproducibility via Thinning) ranks
    genes by the split-half correlation of two independently thinned halves of
    the counts. Both methods support Poisson and Negative Binomial models.
